annotations.caption: Microscopically, there is an endophytic and exophytic papilla.
Myrmecia is a viral wart commonly found on the hands and feet, also known as palmar plantar wart.
The lesion has a mounded appearance and can be found in younger people.
Molluscum bodies are larger and displace the nuclei of keratinocyte.
Comparison of molluscum bodies and myrmecia bodies.
Verruca vulgaris has large nuclei and smaller cytoplasmic inclusions.
Description of physical characteristics of nuclei in keratinocytes and comparison to verruca vulgaris and myrmecia.
Presence of Molluscum bodies, also known as molluscum contagiosum virus particles, which are redder in color than myrmecia.
Herpes simplex type 1 and type 2 produce similar cytopathic changes.
Biopsy was taken from the pink area of the necrotic nasal mucosa.
Diagnosis of herpes simplex virus infection was given based on nuclear features.
Osteoid matrix mineralization with a purple matrix pattern is seen on the far right of the coronary biopsy.
A pleomorphic sarcoma with large hyperchromatic cells is present centrally.
Highly suspicious radiographs for osteosarcoma based on a coronary biopsy. Osteoid matrix mineralization seen on the biopsy.
Abnormal bone osteoid matrix mineralization is seen at higher power.
Pleomorphic sarcoma with large hyperchromatic cells and abnormal bone osteoid matrix mineralization is consistent with osteoblastic osteosarcoma.
